A member of Kiambu county assembly has urged the government to speak with university lecturers to end their current strike. Lari Kirenga MCA Joseph Karichu said lecturers’ demands should not be ignored. The government should pay them better. “They need to live better lives”, Karichu said. Better pay will motivate them.” Karichu said students in public universities have wasted a lot of time due to the strike. The Universities Academic Staff Union embarked started the strike on March 1. The MCA spoke at Nyambare on Tuesday where he presented bursary cheques to 565 needy secondary school and college students.